  "market_context": "After a sell-off from the highs near 44,350, price formed a daily expansion candle with a small wick. Overnight session swept a minor high on the hourly and began falling, suggesting continuation lower toward prior lows around 42,900 and the lower hourly fair value gap.",
  "key_observation": "The daily candle showed an expansion signature with a small wick, and a protected high was confirmed on the lower timeframe by sweeping a high and closing through the up-close candles, enabling a fractal continuation short using 0.5 of the higher timeframe candle as the entry reference.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: On the hourly, identify that the lower half of the higher timeframe candle should respect price, with the hourly fair value gap as the maximum acceptable retracement before continuation lower.",
    "Step 2: Observe the overnight session sweep a small swing high and begin falling, confirming a daily expansion candle setup with a small wick supporting continuation.",
    "Step 3: Search for a protected high on the lower timeframe — confirmed by price sweeping the high and closing through the series of up-close candles.",
    "Step 4: Drop to the 5-minute timeframe and identify the range of up-close candles into the high, with price closing below that range as a change in state of delivery.",
    "Step 5: Enter short on the close, requiring 0.5 of the higher timeframe candle to be respected and allowing price to reach back into the 5-minute fair value gap.",
    "Step 6: Place stop above the fair value gap and target 2R lower."
  ],
  "outcome": "Trade played out as a continuation lower; price nearly stopped out by trading back up into the fair value gap (respecting 0.5 of the HTF candle) but then expanded lower to hit the 2R target.",
  "lessons": "Daily expansion candles with small wicks signal continuation; the fractal model allows entries on lower timeframes by identifying a protected high via change in state of delivery, placing stops above the fair value gap to allow for retracements into 0.5 of the HTF candle.",
